Two ministers from the National Command Council will brief South Africa on the updated regulations of the national lockdown. PRETORIA - Ministers from the National Command Council will brief South Africa on the updated regulations of the national lockdown. READ: Cabinet to discuss COVID-19 responses, relief measures Ministers Nkosazana Dlamini-Zuma, Ronald Lamola and Gwede Mantashe are expected to speak at the briefing. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.